## TL;DR — What a 7 Carat Oval Diamond Ring Actually Costs

**Natural (GIA):** A well-graded 7ct oval in [G-VS2 from Blue Nile](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) runs **[$138,450](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**. Add a setting and you're at **[$139,340](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**. D-VVS1 territory hits **[$241,500](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=D&Clarity=VVS1&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.

**Lab-grown (IGI):** [G-VVS2 IGI oval at $18,247](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-grown-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). D-IF at [$21,483](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-grown-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=D&Clarity=IF&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). That's an **$120,203 spread** for the same face-up size.

**The contrarian truth:** At 7 carats, fewer than 8 GIA-certified oval diamonds with G+ color and VS clarity exist on the open market at any given moment. You are not shopping a commodity — you are selecting from a shortlist. The price you pay is almost entirely determined by which 8 stones happen to exist when you search, not by any rational market formula. That changes how you should negotiate.

