## Final Verdict — Which 7 Carat Oval Diamond Should You Buy?

**Natural buyers:** [GIA G-VS2 at $138,450](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the pick. It sits at the exact intersection of color performance, clarity safety, and price sanity. Step to H only if you're using yellow or rose gold. Step to F only if you're buying for legacy or resale. D-VVS1 at [$241,500](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=D&Clarity=VVS1&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is for investment portfolios and generational jewelry — not daily wear decisions.

**Lab buyers:** [IGI D-IF at $21,483](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-grown-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&Color=D&Clarity=IF&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Buy the best grade available. At lab prices, D-IF costs only [$3,236 more](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-grown-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) than G-VVS2 — that premium is trivial relative to the total purchase.

**Setting:** [Double Pavé in platinum at $1,890](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/double-pave-ring_605074?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The band diamonds frame the stone without competing. Platinum gives you durability proportional to the stone's value.

**Complete ring: [natural $140,340](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [lab $23,373](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-grown-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=7&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

